The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                R. Khan, the driver of the Panskura local that had come within 100m of the East Coast Express on the same track at Sankrail on August 22 , has admitted to overshooting a red signal, South Eastern railway officials said on Friday.     Nepal has banned Indian currency in the denomination of Rs 500 and Rs 1,000. Those travelling to Nepal have been advised to exchange the notes with those of smaller denomination.     Ashima Das, a Bijoygarh resident, died after the motorcycle on which she was riding pillion was hit by a bus on Sarat Bose Road on Friday afternoon. Late on Thursday, a man in his 40s died after being hit by an unidentified vehicle on the Park Circus connector.     Sex worker Shefali Das, 30, was found dead with a cloth around her neck in her room in the red-light area of Sonagachhi on Friday.     Labour secretary R.D. Meena will take over as the land reforms commissioner from Sabyasachi Sen, who will become the chairman of the Public Service Commission.                                                                                                                                               
